`types-aiobotocore[oam]` with services you use in your environment: ```bash python -m pip install 'types-aiobotocore[oam]' ``` - install [lsp-pyright](https://github.com/sublimelsp/lsp-pyright) createlinkinputrequesttypedef: return {...} ``` ## how it works fully automated [mypy-boto3-builder](https://github.com/youtype/mypy_boto3_builder) carefully generates type annotations for each service, patiently waiting for `aiobotocore` updates. it delivers drop-in type annotations for you and makes sure that: - all available `aiobotocore` services are covered. - each public class and method of every `aiobotocore` service gets valid type annotations extracted from `botocore` schemas. - type annotations include up-to-date documentation. - link to documentation is provided for every method. - code is processed by [black](https://github.com/psf/black) and [isort](https://github.com/pycqa/isort) for readability. ## what's new ### implemented features - fully type annotated `boto3`, and `resource` collections - auto discovery of types for `aiobotocore.session.create_client` calls ### latest changes builder changelog can be found in documentation_summary: The HTML text describes the PyPI (Python Package Index) listing for "types-aiobotocore-oam" version 2.12.1, released on March 5, 2024. This package provides type annotations for the aiobotocore.CloudWatchObservabilityAccessManager 2.12.1 service, generated with mypy-boto3-builder 7.23.2. It is designed to enhance code completion and error detection in various IDEs (VSCode, PyCharm, Emacs, Sublime Text) and tools (mypy, pyright) by offering explicit type annotations for aiobotocore services. The package supports Python versions 3.8 and above and is licensed under the MIT License. Installation instructions are provided for different environments and IDEs, emphasizing the ease of integrating type checking and code completion for aiobotocore code. The project is maintained by Vlad Emelianov and encourages contributions and feedback through the mypy-boto3-builder repository.
